The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring July 19 through July 25, 2015, as Captive Nations Week. The proclamation emphasizes the United States' commitment to democracy and freedom, stating that all people have the right to choose their own destiny. It acknowledges the progress made in terms of economic development and the transition from dictatorships to democracies but also highlights the challenges faced, such as territorial disputes, human rights violations, technological advancements aiding oppressive regimes, and economic inequality. The United States pledges to use its power to support democracies, promote economic reforms, and advocate for open and honest elections and independent judiciaries. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to reaffirm their commitment to freedom, dignity, and opportunity for all.